@node "MENUES" "Menues"
@toc "MENU"

@{b}11.1 Project Menu@{ub}

 @{fg shine}New@{fg text}
    Creates a new archive. If you have any unsaved changes
    AlbIn_MUI will warn you. You can then either choose to
    clear the memory or save and then clear or cancel the action.



 @{fg shine}Open...@{fg text}
    A file requester is prompting you to select an
    archive to be loaded in to the memory. This version of
    AlbIn_MUI is only using the RAM memory for storing the data.
    In later versions AlbIn_MUI will be able to read/write
    the data directly off the drive where you store it.



 @{fg shine}Append...@{fg text}
    Adds a previously saved database to the current
    database. N.B. Duplicates may occur. AlbIn_MUI
    does not check for duplicates, so you have to remove them
    manually.



 @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
    Saves the archive with the current name. If you have
    choosen to 'Ask first' in the 'prefs' window then AlbIn_MUI
    will always ask if you will overwrite the old archive with the
    same name, if you haven't choosen that option, AlbIn_MUI
    will simply overwrite the old archive without warning. If the
    archive doesn't have a name, then this option will be the same
    as 'Save as'.



 @{fg shine}Save as...@{fg text}
    Let you save an archive with a different name.
    This option should also be used the first time (even if you don't
    know about it). If an archive with the name that you selected then
    AlbIn_MUI will ask you if you want to replace the old archive
    or give it another name (or you can cancel the action as always).



 @{fg shine}Export...@{fg text}
    Export the arcive to three different destinations.
    Read more about export under @{" ExportáWindow " link "EXPORTWINDOW" 0}.
    


 @{fg shine}About...@{fg text}
    Displays a requester with information about AlbIn_MUI.



 @{fg shine}Quit...@{fg text}
    Exit AlbIn_MUI. If you have unsaved changes
    then AlbIn_MUI will warn you before the exit. You can also
    cancel this action if you have these unsaved changes.




@{b}11.2 Sort Menu@{ub}



 @{fg shine}Seperate Formats @{fg text}
    If you want to sort every format of
    albums for them self, then this option should be marked.
    If you don't mark this option the 'format' cycle gadget
    will be ignored when sorting the albums.



 @{fg shine}Artist -- Title @{fg text}
    Sorting by the 'Artist' field in the
    main window. The second criteria is the 'Title' field in the
    same window.



 @{fg shine}Artist -- Date @{fg text}
    Sorting by the 'Artist' field in the main
    window (just like above) and then by the 'Release Date' field
    in the 'Album Comments' window. It's a good idea to have
    the year first and an additional date later so.



 @{fg shine}Title -- Artist @{fg text}
    Sorting with the 'Title' first and then
    the 'Artist'.



 @{fg shine}Rec. Comp. -- Date @{fg text}
    Sorting by the 'Record Company'
    field in the 'Album Comments' window and then the 'Release
    Date' field in the same window.



 @{fg shine}Rec. Comp. -- Cat. Nr. @{fg text}
    Sorting by the 'Record Company'
    field in the 'Album Comments' window and then the
    'Catalouge Number' in the same window.



 @{fg shine}Time -- Artist @{fg text}
    Sorting by the 'Play Time' field in the
    main window and then by the 'Artist' field in the same
    window.




@{b}11.3 Album Menu@{ub}



 @{fg shine}New @{fg text}
    Makes a new album-entry in the list. This will be
    inserted last.



 @{fg shine}Insert @{fg text}
    Inserts a new album after the selected album.



 @{fg shine}Delete...@{fg text}
    Deletes the selected album. Arequester
    will ask you if you really want to delete this album.



 @{fg shine}Next@{fg text}
    Steps one album forward -- to the next album in the list.



 @{fg shine}Prev@{fg text}
    Steps one album backward -- to the previous album in the list.



 @{fg shine}First@{fg text}
    Jumps to the first item in the list over albums.



 @{fg shine}Last@{fg text}
    Jumps to the last item in the list over albums.




@{b}11.4 Misc Menu@{ub}



 @{fg shine}Find...@{fg text}
    Shows the @{" 'Find'áwindow " link "FINDWINDOW" 0}.
    This window is also shown if you select 'Find Next' without
    anything in the searchstring gadget.)



 @{fg shine}Find Next @{fg text}
    Finds the next item that matches the search
    criteria. It searches from the selected album to the end of
    the database.



 @{fg shine}Guide Preview @{fg text}
    Generates a preview of the exported
    guide. The format is controlled by the @{" 'Export'áwindow " link "EXPORTWINDOW" 0}.



 @{fg shine}Prefs...@{fg text}
    Shows the @{" 'Preferences'áwindow " link "PREFSWINDOW" 0}.




@{b}11.5 Open/Activate Menu@{ub}



 @{fg shine}Album...@{fg text}
    Opens the @{" 'Album'áwindow " link "ALBWINDOW" 0}. This is always open so
    this short cut is only activating the window. 



 @{fg shine}Song...@{fg text}
    Opens the @{" 'Song'áwindow " link "SONGWINDOW" 0}. This is one of the two
    windws with a list gadget.



 @{fg shine}Album Comments...@{fg text}
    Opens the @{" 'AlbumáComments'áwindow " link "ALBCOMWINDOW" 0}.



 @{fg shine}Song Comments...@{fg text}
    Opens the @{" 'SongáComments'áwindow " link "SONGCOMWINDOW" 0}. 



 @{fg shine}Artist Info...@{fg text}
    Opens the @{" 'ArtistáInfo'áwindow " link "ARTISTWINDOW" 0}. This is the
    second window with a list gadget. 



 @{fg shine}Artist-Title List...@{fg text}
    Opens the window with the list over albums.
    See @{" Artist-TitleáList " link "ATLISTWINDOW" 0} for more detail.




@{b}11.6 Artist-Title List@{ub}


 The selected album will always be marked in the artist-title
 window, but you can also select more than one album at a time.  If
 you multi-select albums (by dragging the mouse with the left button
 pressed in the artist-title window) you manipulate the block in
 three ways, save it and move it up or down in the list (if wan't to
 override the sort routine).

 @{fg shine}Save Selected As...@{fg text}
    Saves the selected entries in the @{" Artist-TitleáList " link "ATLISTWINDOW" 0}.



 @{fg shine}Delete Selected...@{fg text}
    Deletes the selected entries in the @{" Artist-TitleáList " link "ATLISTWINDOW" 0}.


 @{fg shine}Move Selected Up @{fg text}
    Move the selected entry in the @{" Artist-TitleáList " link "ATLISTWINDOW" 0} 
    upwards (backwards) if possible.



 @{fg shine}Move Selected Down @{fg text}
    Move the selected entry in the @{" Artist-TitleáList " link "ATLISTWINDOW" 0} 
    downwards (forwards) if possible.

@endnode

